JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- The Houston Texans (1-4) take on the Jacksonville Jaguars (1-4) at EverBank Field Sunday in an AFC South showdown. 
The Texans have activated defensive end J.J. Watt as he was previously listed as questionable with an illness. Meanwhile, the Jaguars announced Sunday morning that running back T.J. Yeldon is out for the game with a groin injury.
